general_exclusion_criteria:
History of splenectomy (unless approved by principal investigator);
Allergic reaction to ruxolitinib or related compound;
Concurrent use of strong cytochrome P450 3A4 inhibitor medicines;
Receipt of any other investigational agent;
Uncontrolled intercurrent acute illness;
Inadequate hepatic function (AST/ALT >3× ULN) or renal function (creatinine > ULN or GFR <60 mL/min/1.73 m²);
Pregnancy, lactation, or lack of agreement to use adequate contraception for persons of reproductive potential;
Active severe cardiovascular disease (NYHA functional class worse than IIb);
Psychiatric or social conditions limiting adherence to study protocols.

