Patients with a history of bilateral Wilms tumour (synchronous or metachronous);
Uncontrolled intercurrent illnesses including active infections;
Symptomatic congestive heart failure Grade ≥ 2 CTCAE v5.0;
Renal tubular acidosis (serum HCO₃⁻ < 16 mmol/L and PO₄³⁻ ≤ 2 mg/dL or < 0.8 mmol/L) for high-/very‑high‑risk relapsed FHWT;
Chronic inflammatory bowel disease and/or intestinal obstruction for stages II‑IV DAWT and standard‑risk relapsed FHWT;
Concomitant use of St. John’s Wort unable to discontinue;
Pregnancy in female participants;
Breastfeeding lactation in female participants;
Failure to agree to effective contraception for sexually active individuals of reproductive potential.

