Uncontrolled intercurrent illness including active infection, symptomatic congestive heart failure, unstable angina, cardiac arrhythmia, or serious psychiatric or social circumstances compromising safety of biopsy or surgery.;
Pregnancy;
Uncorrectable bleeding or coagulation disorders posing excessive risk for percutaneous or surgical procedures.

History of serious medical, laboratory, psychiatric, or social condition interfering with consent;
Pregnancy, lactation, or intent to become pregnant/planning to breastfeed;
Known central nervous system involvement by Waldenström macroglobulinemia;
Human immunodeficiency virus infection;
Active hepatitis B virus infection (positive HBsAg or HBV DNA+) or active hepatitis C virus infection (detectable HCV RNA);
Concurrent systemic immunosuppressive therapy exceeding prednisone <20 mg/day equivalent;
Active or ongoing autoimmune hemolytic anemia or immune-mediated thrombocytopenia;
Concomitant anticoagulation with warfarin or warfarin derivatives;
Receipt of live, attenuated vaccination within four weeks preceding study drug dosing;
Uncontrolled acute bacterial, viral, fungal, or parasitic infection (excluding superficial fungal nail infection);
Major surgical procedure within four weeks before first dose;
Severe inherited or acquired bleeding diatheses, recent cerebrovascular accident or intracranial haemorrhage within six months;
Incapacity to ingest oral medication tablets;
Unable to comply with scheduled outpatient assessments and follow‑up;
Significant untreated cardiovascular disease (recent unstable angina, myocardial infarction within six months, left ventricular ejection fraction ≤ 45 %, NYHA class III–IV heart failure, life‑threatening arrhythmias);
Hypersensitivity to any components of zanubrutinib, bendamustine, or rituximab;
Non‑compliance with prescribed therapeutic regimen jeopardizing safety or data integrity;
Other malignant neoplasm diagnosed within three years (exceptions: adequately treated basal or squamous cell skin cancer, non‑muscle invasive bladder cancer, cervical intraepithelial neoplasia grade II/III, ductal carcinoma in situ of breast, or localized Gleason score 6 prostate cancer);
Severe or disabling pulmonary disease;
Ongoing illicit drug/alcohol dependence or unmanaged psychiatric disorder compromising adherence;
Use of potent cytochrome P450 3A enzyme inducers.

Pregnant women;
Individuals living with HIV who are taking combination antiretroviral therapy;
Uncontrolled intercurrent illnesses such as symptomatic heart failure, unstable angina, myocardial infarction, arrhythmias, pulmonary fibrosis, or clinically significant infections;
Laboratory values indicating inadequate bone marrow reserve, renal function, or hepatic function beyond protocol-defined limits (e.g., white blood cell count < 2.5×10^9/L, platelets < 80×10^9/L, serum bilirubin > 2 times ULN);
Inability to give informed consent or comply with study procedures.

history of a malignant disease other than melanoma;
untreated, active, or symptomatic central nervous system metastases or carcinomatous meningitis;
hypersensitivity to imc-f106c, nivolumab, relatlimab, or any formulation excipient;
clinically significant pulmonary disease or impaired lung function;
clinically significant cardiac disease or impaired cardiac function;
active autoimmune disease requiring immunosuppressive treatment;
any medical condition that is poorly controlled or that would jeopardize safe participation, adherence to protocol, or data integrity.

