Disease transformed to aggressive lymphoma;
Symptomatic or suspected hyperviscosity syndrome with IgM >4000 mg/dL when plasmatherapy unavailable;
Receipt of any other investigational anticancer agent;
Persistent (>Grade 1) toxicities from prior anticancer therapy (except alopecia or peripheral neuropathy);
Active uncontrolled infection requiring inpatient care or IV antimicrobials within 4 weeks;
Severe cardiovascular disease (NYHA class III–IV heart failure, left ventricular ejection fraction < 45 %, unstable angina, myocardial infarction <6 months ago, uncontrolled arrhythmias);
Significant neurological comorbidity (seizure disorder, cerebrovascular accident/stroke, psychosis, dementia, central nervous system vasculitis, encephalitis);
Requirement for supplemental oxygen at rest to keep SpO₂ > 92 %;
Recent (<28 days) chronic immunosuppressive therapy for non‑study indications, including systemic glucocorticoids ≥20 mg/day prednisone equivalents;
Known or presumed central nervous system involvement or leptomeningeal disease from Waldenström macroglobulinemia;
Pregnancy, lactation, or inability/unwillingness to comply with mandated contraception measures;
Current substance/alcohol dependence, untreated major psychiatric illness, or socially unstable circumstance limiting protocol adherence;
History of hypersensitivity to substances chemically or biologically similar to epcoritamab;
Administration of a live or live‑attenuated vaccine within 4 weeks.

History of severe allergic or anaphylactic reaction to humanized or murine monoclonal antibodies or mouse-derived products;
Grade > 1 peripheral neuropathy or demyelinating Charcot‑Marie‑Tooth disease;
Primary or secondary central nervous system lymphoma at enrolment or prior history thereof;
Contraindication to any component of Pola‑R‑CHP or glofitamab;
Significant or extensive cardiovascular disease;
Clinically significant hepatic impairment;
Uncontrolled concurrent illness affecting participation;
Recent major surgery (within four weeks);
Live attenuated vaccination within four weeks preceding dosing or anticipated thereafter;
Any active infection impacting safety;
Suspected active or latent Mycobacterium tuberculosis infection;
Positive serology for chronic hepatitis B, hepatitis C, or Human T‑lymphotropic Virus‑1;
Past or present progressive multifocal leukoencephalopathy;
Active autoimmune disease requiring systemic therapy.

Active uncontrolled or symptomatic central nervous system metastases or leptomeningeal disease;
History of interstitial lung disease or pneumonitis requiring steroid treatment, or currently existing ILD/pneumonitis;
Significant cardiac disease including New York Heart Association class II–IV heart failure, left ventricular ejection fraction < 55%, uncontrolled hypertension, clinically meaningful arrhythmias, or QTc prolongation (>470 ms females, >450 ms males);
Severe pulmonary comorbidity (e.g., recent pulmonary embolism, severe COPD, restrictive lung disease, ongoing pneumonia, prior pneumonectomy);
Uncontrolled infectious diseases including active hepatitis B, hepatitis C, or HIV infection;
Pregnancy, lactation, or inability/unwillingness to use adequate contraception;
Concurrent malignant disease within the preceding five years (with exceptions noted);
Inadequate organ function exceeding specified laboratory limits (hematologic, hepatic, renal, coagulation parameters);
Performance status worse than ECOG 1.

History of invasive breast carcinoma prior to study entry;
Use of any other investigational agents for breast cancer;
Major surgical procedure (except vascular access) or significant trauma within 28 days preceding enrollment or planned during study;
Extracranial palliative radiotherapy within 7 days before enrollment;
Allergic reaction to trastuzumab, pertuzumab, paclitaxel, nab-paclitaxel, docetaxel, trastuzumab deruxtecan, ado‐trastuzumab emtansine, or tucatinib;
Myocardial infarction within 6 months or symptomatic congestive heart failure (New York Heart Association class II–IV);
Untreated intracranial lesions on baseline MRI (unless sponsor approval obtained);
Systemic glucocorticoid use exceeding 2 mg/day dexamethasone-equivalent for brain metastasis symptom control;
Leptomeningeal disease evident on MRI;
Uncontrolled seizures (>once weekly) or poorly managed epilepsy;
Clinically significant cardiac arrhythmias requiring intervention (grade 3 or higher) or uncontrolled atrial fibrillation;
Past or current interstitial lung disease/pneumonitis needing steroids or unable to exclude via imaging;
Significant existing pulmonary pathology (recent PE, severe COPD, restrictive disease, pleural effusions, etc.);
Active autoimmune/connective tissue disease with pulmonary involvement;
Previous pneumonectomy;
Active, uncontrolled serious infection;
Inability to ingest oral tablets or substantial GI disease impairing drug absorption;
Ongoing grade 2 or greater diarrhea of any cause;
Concomitant use of potent CYP2C8 or CYP3A4 enzyme inhibitors or inducers;
Pregnancy or lactation.

Patients who have not recovered from prior therapy–related adverse events greater than Grade 1 (excluding alopecia and fatigue);
Active immunodeficiency including HIV/AIDS;
Active hepatitis B virus infection or active hepatitis C virus infection;
Known active Mycobacterium tuberculosis infection;
Concurrent actively progressing malignancy or malignancy requiring active treatment (exceptions: cured basal/squamous cell skin cancer, in‑situ cervical cancer);
Active autoimmune disease requiring systemic treatment within the preceding 2 years (physiological hormone replacements exempt);
History or evidence of active non‑infectious pneumonitis;
Any active infection necessitating systemic antimicrobial therapy;
Significant psychiatric illness or substance misuse impairing compliance;
Pregnancy, lactation, or intent to become pregnant/father a child during the study window up to 120 days after last dose;
Contraindications to magnetic resonance imaging of the brain (e.g., implanted devices incompatible with MRI, allergic reaction to gadolinium contrast);
Receipt of a live viral vaccine within 30 days before initiating study drug.

