History of another malignancy within three years (except adequately treated basal/squamous cell skin cancer, in situ lesions, or cured low-risk prostate cancer);
Known central nervous system involvement;
Active or untreated graft‑versus‑host disease;
Uncontrolled cardiovascular disorders (uncontrolled hypertension, arrhythmia, symptomatic heart failure, unstable angina, recent myocardial infarction or thrombotic events);
Active systemic infection requiring intravenous antibiotics;
Positive testing for active HIV, hepatitis B, or hepatitis C infection (active viral replication);
Pregnancy or breastfeeding;
Inability to safely receive required concomitant supportive measures (thromboprophylaxis, adequate hematologic counts despite prohibited growth factor/transfusion windows);
Severe hypersensitivity to study drugs or related compounds;
Any condition judged by investigator to pose undue safety risk or interfere with adherence to study protocols.

Inoperable locally advanced or metastatic breast cancer;
Pathologic complete response after neoadjuvant therapy;
History of any other cancer except non‑melanoma skin cancer or cervical intraepithelial neoplasia deemed low risk, unless in complete remission off therapy ≥ 5 years;
Severe or uncontrolled systemic disease compromising participation;
Left ventricular ejection fraction < 50% or New York Heart Association Class II or higher heart failure;
Mean resting QTcF interval > 480 ms at screening;
Concurrent exogenous reproductive hormone therapy or non‑topical hormonal therapy for non‑cancer indications;
Any concurrent anti‑cancer treatment not specified in the protocol (aside from bisphosphonates or denosumab);
Pregnancy or lactation;
Known hypersensitivity to camizestrant, related compounds, or to luteinizing‑hormone releasing hormone agonists where applicable.

